<exercise id="fs-idm378134192">
<problem id="fs-idm382694048">
<para id="fs-idm372986256"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67897"/>Explain the difference between depreciation, depletion, and amortization.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm389399392">
<para id="fs-idm391843872">Depreciation is the process of allocating the cost of using a long-term asset over its anticipated economic (useful) life, whereas depletion is the process of expensing the cost of natural resources over the life of the asset, typically using a unit-consumed method. Amortization is specifically for intangible assets and typically is calculated using straight-line with no salvage value.</para>
</solution>
